   <concept id="FAR_12_102" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">12.102</ph> Applicability.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d678e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d705e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> This part shall be used for the
acquisition of supplies or services that meet the definitions of “commercial
product” or “commercial service” at <xref href="2.101.dita#FAR_2_101"
                        base="i1125359"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d705e18">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> Contracting
officers shall use the policies in this part in conjunction with
the policies and procedures for solicitation, evaluation and award
prescribed in <xref href="Part_13.dita#FAR_Part_13"
                        base="i1112458"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  13</xref>, Simplified
Acquisition Procedures; <xref href="Part_14.dita#FAR_Part_14"
                        base="i1111055"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  14</xref>,
Sealed Bidding; or <xref href="Part_15.dita#FAR_Part_15"
                        base="i1109360"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  15</xref>,
Contracting by Negotiation, as appropriate for the particular acquisition.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d705e32">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph> Contracts
for the acquisition of commercial
products or commercial services are subject to the policies
in other parts of the FAR. When a policy in another part of the
FAR is inconsistent with a policy in this part, this <xref href="Part_12.dita#FAR_Part_12"
                        base="i1113784"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  12</xref> shall take
precedence for the acquisition of commercial products or
commercial services.
               </p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d705e40">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph> The definition
of commercial product uses
the phrase “purposes other than governmental purposes”. These purposes are
those that are not unique to a government.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d705e45">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(e)</ph> This part
shall not apply to the acquisition of commercial products or
commercial services—
               </p>
               <ol id="d678e77" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d705e51">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> At or below the micro-purchase
threshold;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d705e56">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Using the <xref href="https://www.gsa.gov/forms-library/us-government-purchase-order-invoice-voucher"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">Standard Form 44</xref> (see <xref href="13.306.dita#FAR_13_306"
                              base="i1111753"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">13.306</xref>);</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d705e67">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> Using the
imprest fund (see <xref href="13.305.dita#FAR_13_305"
                              base="i1111714"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">13.305</xref>);</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d705e75">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph> Using the
Governmentwide commercial purchase card as a method of purchase
rather than only as a method of payment; or</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d705e80">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph> Directly
from another Federal agency.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d705e85">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(f)</ph>
               </p>
               <ol id="d678e144" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d705e90">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> Contracting
officers may treat any acquisition of supplies or services that,
as determined by the head of the agency, are to be used to facilitate
defense against or recovery from cyber, nuclear, biological, chemical,
or radiological attack, as an acquisition of commercial products or
commercial services.
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d705e95">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        <ph rev="FAC 2025-06 October 1, 2025" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2024-001?>A contract in an amount greater than $25 million that is awarded on a sole source basis for a product or service treated as a commercial product or commercial service under paragraph (f)(1) of this section but does not meet the definition of a commercial product or commercial service at <xref href="2.101.dita#FAR_2_101"
                                 base="i1125359"
                                 outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                 class="- topic/xref ">2.101</xref> shall not be exempt from—<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 12.102 by revising paragraph (f)(2).?></ph>
                     </p>
                     <ol id="d678e166" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d705e104">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph> Cost accounting standards (see <xref href="Subpart_30.2.dita#FAR_Subpart_30_2"
                                    base="i1087111"
                                    outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">subpart  30.2</xref>); or
                           </p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d705e112">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph> Certified
cost or pricing data requirements (see <xref href="15.403.dita#FAR_15_403"
                                    base="i1105934"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">15.403</xref>).</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
